@startuml
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/main/proveo.puml
title Leases & Grants
' Paper: Gray & Cheriton, Leases — Fault-Tolerant Distributed Cache Consistency, SOSP 1989
' URL:   https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/74850.74870
' Paper: Burrows, The Chubby Lock Service, OSDI 2006
' URL:   https://www.usenix.org/conference/osdi-06/chubby-lock-service-loosely-coupled-distributed-systems
' Spec:  OAuth 2.0 (scoped delegation), RFC 6749
' Level: 4
' Provenance: projects/aphelion · session/types_continuation.go, capability_store.go

component "Proposal\n(model asks)"             as PROP  <<app>>
actor     "Operator approval"                  as OP
component "Lease\n(scope · TTL · turn-budget)" as LEASE <<db>>
component "Per-turn consumption"               as USE   <<app>>
component "Expired / spent"                    as EXP   <<error>>

PROP  ARROW_MAIN     OP    : request
OP    ARROW_MAIN     LEASE : grant (bounded)
LEASE ARROW_MAIN     USE   : consume one turn
USE   ARROW_OPTIONAL LEASE : decrement budget
LEASE ARROW_ERROR    EXP   : TTL elapsed / budget 0

note bottom of LEASE
  A grant is **consumable, time-bounded, non-self-renewing** —
  spent per turn, never a blank check. Re-grant needs a new approval.
end note
@enduml
